# Default quantile plot

<pre class="mcode">
m <-
  ggplot(mpg, aes(displ, 1 / hwy)) +
  geom_point()
p <-  m + geom_quantile()

plotly::ggplotly(p)
</pre>

You can do the same with a sequence.

<pre class="mcode">
m <-
  ggplot(mpg, aes(displ, 1 / hwy)) +
  geom_point()
q10 <- seq(0.05, 0.95, by = 0.05)
p <-  m + geom_quantile(quantiles = q10)

plotly::ggplotly(p)
</pre>

Note that rqss doesn't pick a smoothing constant automatically, so you will need to tweak lambda manually.

<pre class="mcode">
m <-
  ggplot(mpg, aes(displ, 1 / hwy)) +
  geom_point()
p <-  m + geom_quantile(method = "rqss", lambda = 0.1)

plotly::ggplotly(p)
</pre>

# Setting aesthetics


<pre class="mcode">
m <-
  ggplot(mpg, aes(displ, 1 / hwy)) +
  geom_point()
p <-  m + geom_quantile(colour = "red", size = 2, alpha = 0.5)

plotly::ggplotly(p)
</pre>
